<DOC><DOCNO> AP890530-0031 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-30-89 0340EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Japan-DiscountRate     05-30 0113</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Japan-Discount Rate,0114</SECOND><HEAD>Japan Raises Discount Rate for First Time in 9 Years</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Japan's central bank today announced it will raiseits official discount rate by 0.75 percentage points to 3.25percent, reversing the easy money policy it maintained for almost adecade.   The decision, which clearly shows the central bank's intentionto combat inflation, will also lead to rises in interest andlending rates from commercial banks, and housing loans starting inmid-June.   Effective Wednesday, the official discount rate, the Bank ofJapan's lending rate to commercial banks, rises to 3.25 percentfrom the current 2.5 percent, the lowest among the Group of Sevenindustrial nations, officials said.</TEXT></DOC>